Ecuador head coach Gustavo Alfaro has unveiled his squad for the international friendly against the Super Eagles of Nigeria. Veteran forward; Enner Valencia, Pervis Estupian and Moises Caicedo are some of the top stars in the 25-man squad. The encounter is billed for the Red Bull Arena, New Jersey on June 2. It is the first time both countries will meet at the senior level. La Tri will also take on Mexico and Cape Verde on June 5 and June 11 respectively. THE FULL SQUAD Goalkeepers
Hernan Galindez, Moises Ramirez, Alexander Dominguez Defenders
Robert Arboleda, Piero Hincapie, Felix Tores, Xavier Arreaga, Diego Palacios, Bryon Castillo, Jackson Corozo, Pervis Estupian Midfielders
Alexander Alvarado, Alan Franco, Gonzalo Plata, Dixon Arroyo, Romario Ibarra, Jeremy Sarmiento, Moises Caicedo, Angel Mena, Jose Cifuentes, Jhegson Mendez, Forwards
Leonardo Campana, Michael Estrada, Djorkaeff Reasco, Enner Valencia.